results.description: When photographing the forest area of Ramsholmen, Raasepori, Finland last summer, a local shower surprised me. I was walking a narrow path and took cover under the trees as it started to rain. I felt an urgent need to look behind me, and when I turned, I didn´t see the forest deer (Capreolus capreolus) at first, but then I saw the magnificent animal. He/she was standing only about 15 meters from me. I moved really slowly. The rain softened the sounds of the noisy old camera. For a brief moment we watched each other, I got the photo and then the deer ran away. Magical feeling.
